1. Replace content/_index.md. Right now it ships with Jan Raasch's marketing copy: "There is a website obesity
crisis... Made with 💟 by Jan Raasch." If you deploy now, your homepage is literally Jan's blog about his theme. This
 is the most embarrassing thing in the project.

2. Replace description in hugo.toml. Currently "Hugo + Bear = :heart:" — also bearblog's example. This text shows up:
- In <meta name="description"> (Google snippets)
- In <meta property="og:description"> (Twitter/Slack/Telegram link previews)
- In the homepage RSS feed
Pick one sentence about your blog.

3. Delete or rewrite the placeholder posts. content/blog/hello.md is "This is a page about »Hello«" and
content/blog/markdown-syntax.md is the bearblog demo Lorem-ipsum. If you deploy and someone clicks them, they see
filler. Either delete both, or rename one to lorem.md with draft: true so it stays as a local-only formatting test.

Critical: missing assets that 404 right now

4. Change the OpenGraph share image. images = ["images/share.png"]. A 1200×630 PNG with your blog name on it is the bare minimum. Same path: static/images/share.png.

Pre-deploy hygiene

Lower priority — can happen after deploy

- Google Search Console verification + submit /sitemap.xml (within a week of deploy is fine)
- Bing Webmaster + IndexNow via Cloudflare's integration (one toggle in CF dashboard)
- Cloudflare Web Analytics (privacy-friendly, no cookie banner needed)
